2991
2992arena_t *
2993arena_new(unsigned ind)
2994{
2995 arena_t *arena;
2996 unsigned i;
2997 arena_bin_t *bin;
2998
2999 /*
3000 * Allocate arena, arena->lstats, and arena->hstats contiguously, mainly
3001 * because there is no way to clean up if base_alloc() OOMs.
3002 */
3003 if (config_stats) {
3004 arena = (arena_t *)base_alloc(CACHELINE_CEILING(sizeof(arena_t))
3005 + QUANTUM_CEILING(nlclasses * sizeof(malloc_large_stats_t) +
3006 nhclasses) * sizeof(malloc_huge_stats_t));
3007 } else
3008 arena = (arena_t *)base_alloc(sizeof(arena_t));
3009 if (arena == NULL)
3010 return (NULL);
3011
3012 arena->ind = ind;
3013 arena->nthreads = 0;
3014 if (malloc_mutex_init(&arena->lock))
3015 return (NULL);
3016
3017 if (config_stats) {
3018 memset(&arena->stats, 0, sizeof(arena_stats_t));
3019 arena->stats.lstats = (malloc_large_stats_t *)((uintptr_t)arena
3020 + CACHELINE_CEILING(sizeof(arena_t)));
3021 memset(arena->stats.lstats, 0, nlclasses *
3022 sizeof(malloc_large_stats_t));
3023 arena->stats.hstats = (malloc_huge_stats_t *)((uintptr_t)arena
3024 + CACHELINE_CEILING(sizeof(arena_t)) +
3025 QUANTUM_CEILING(nlclasses * sizeof(malloc_large_stats_t)));
3026 memset(arena->stats.hstats, 0, nhclasses *
3027 sizeof(malloc_huge_stats_t));
3028 if (config_tcache)
3029 ql_new(&arena->tcache_ql);
3030 }
3031
3032 if (config_prof)
3033 arena->prof_accumbytes = 0;
3034
3035 if (config_cache_oblivious) {
3036 /*
3037 * A nondeterministic seed based on the address of arena reduces
3038 * the likelihood of lockstep non-uniform cache index
3039 * utilization among identical concurrent processes, but at the
3040 * cost of test repeatability. For debug builds, instead use a
3041 * deterministic seed.
3042 */
3043 arena->offset_state = config_debug ? ind :
3044 (uint64_t)(uintptr_t)arena;
3045 }
3046
3047 arena->dss_prec = chunk_dss_prec_get();
3048
3049 arena->spare = NULL;
3050
3051 arena->lg_dirty_mult = arena_lg_dirty_mult_default_get();
3052 arena->purging = false;
3053 arena->nactive = 0;
3054 arena->ndirty = 0;
3055
3056 arena_avail_tree_new(&arena->runs_avail);
3057 qr_new(&arena->runs_dirty, rd_link);
3058 qr_new(&arena->chunks_cache, cc_link);
3059
3060 ql_new(&arena->huge);
3061 if (malloc_mutex_init(&arena->huge_mtx))
3062 return (NULL);
3063
3064 extent_tree_szad_new(&arena->chunks_szad_cached);
3065 extent_tree_ad_new(&arena->chunks_ad_cached);
3066 extent_tree_szad_new(&arena->chunks_szad_retained);
3067 extent_tree_ad_new(&arena->chunks_ad_retained);
3068 if (malloc_mutex_init(&arena->chunks_mtx))
3069 return (NULL);
3070 ql_new(&arena->node_cache);
3071 if (malloc_mutex_init(&arena->node_cache_mtx))
3072 return (NULL);
3073
3074 arena->chunk_hooks = chunk_hooks_default;
3075
3076 /* Initialize bins. */
3077 for (i = 0; i < NBINS; i++) {
3078 bin = &arena->bins[i];
3079 if (malloc_mutex_init(&bin->lock))
3080 return (NULL);
3081 bin->runcur = NULL;
3082 arena_run_tree_new(&bin->runs);
3083 if (config_stats)
3084 memset(&bin->stats, 0, sizeof(malloc_bin_stats_t));
3085 }
3086
3087 return (arena);
3088}
3089
3090/*
3091 * Calculate bin_info->run_size such that it meets the following constraints:
3092 *
3093 * *) bin_info->run_size <= arena_maxrun
3094 * *) bin_info->nregs <= RUN_MAXREGS
3095 *
3096 * bin_info->nregs and bin_info->reg0_offset are also calculated here, since
3097 * these settings are all interdependent.
3098 */
3099static void
3100bin_info_run_size_calc(arena_bin_info_t *bin_info)
3101{
3102 size_t pad_size;
3103 size_t try_run_size, perfect_run_size, actual_run_size;
3104 uint32_t try_nregs, perfect_nregs, actual_nregs;
3105
3106 /*
3107 * Determine redzone size based on minimum alignment and minimum
3108 * redzone size. Add padding to the end of the run if it is needed to
3109 * align the regions. The padding allows each redzone to be half the
3110 * minimum alignment; without the padding, each redzone would have to
3111 * be twice as large in order to maintain alignment.
3112 */
3113 if (config_fill && unlikely(opt_redzone)) {
3114 size_t align_min = ZU(1) << (jemalloc_ffs(bin_info->reg_size) -
3115 1);
3116 if (align_min <= REDZONE_MINSIZE) {
3117 bin_info->redzone_size = REDZONE_MINSIZE;
3118 pad_size = 0;
3119 } else {
3120 bin_info->redzone_size = align_min >> 1;
3121 pad_size = bin_info->redzone_size;
3122 }
3123 } else {
3124 bin_info->redzone_size = 0;
3125 pad_size = 0;
3126 }
3127 bin_info->reg_interval = bin_info->reg_size +
3128 (bin_info->redzone_size << 1);
3129
3130 /*
3131 * Compute run size under ideal conditions (no redzones, no limit on run
3132 * size).
3133 */
3134 try_run_size = PAGE;
3135 try_nregs = try_run_size / bin_info->reg_size;
3136 do {
3137 perfect_run_size = try_run_size;
3138 perfect_nregs = try_nregs;
3139
3140 try_run_size += PAGE;
3141 try_nregs = try_run_size / bin_info->reg_size;
3142 } while (perfect_run_size != perfect_nregs * bin_info->reg_size);
3143 assert(perfect_nregs <= RUN_MAXREGS);
3144
3145 actual_run_size = perfect_run_size;
3146 actual_nregs = (actual_run_size - pad_size) / bin_info->reg_interval;
3147
3148 /*
3149 * Redzones can require enough padding that not even a single region can
3150 * fit within the number of pages that would normally be dedicated to a
3151 * run for this size class. Increase the run size until at least one
3152 * region fits.
3153 */
3154 while (actual_nregs == 0) {
3155 assert(config_fill && unlikely(opt_redzone));
3156
3157 actual_run_size += PAGE;
3158 actual_nregs = (actual_run_size - pad_size) /
3159 bin_info->reg_interval;
3160 }
3161
3162 /*
3163 * Make sure that the run will fit within an arena chunk.
3164 */
3165 while (actual_run_size > arena_maxrun) {
3166 actual_run_size -= PAGE;
3167 actual_nregs = (actual_run_size - pad_size) /
3168 bin_info->reg_interval;
3169 }
3170 assert(actual_nregs > 0);
3171 assert(actual_run_size == s2u(actual_run_size));
3172
3173 /* Copy final settings. */
3174 bin_info->run_size = actual_run_size;
3175 bin_info->nregs = actual_nregs;
3176 bin_info->reg0_offset = actual_run_size - (actual_nregs *
3177 bin_info->reg_interval) - pad_size + bin_info->redzone_size;
3178
3179 if (actual_run_size > small_maxrun)
3180 small_maxrun = actual_run_size;
3181
3182 assert(bin_info->reg0_offset - bin_info->redzone_size + (bin_info->nregs
3183 * bin_info->reg_interval) + pad_size == bin_info->run_size);
3184}

3230
3231bool
3232arena_boot(void)
3233{
3234 unsigned i;
3235
3236 arena_lg_dirty_mult_default_set(opt_lg_dirty_mult);
3237
3238 /*
3239 * Compute the header size such that it is large enough to contain the
3240 * page map. The page map is biased to omit entries for the header
3241 * itself, so some iteration is necessary to compute the map bias.
3242 *
3243 * 1) Compute safe header_size and map_bias values that include enough
3244 * space for an unbiased page map.
3245 * 2) Refine map_bias based on (1) to omit the header pages in the page
3246 * map. The resulting map_bias may be one too small.
3247 * 3) Refine map_bias based on (2). The result will be >= the result
3248 * from (2), and will always be correct.
3249 */
3250 map_bias = 0;
3251 for (i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
3252 size_t header_size = offsetof(arena_chunk_t, map_bits) +
3253 ((sizeof(arena_chunk_map_bits_t) +
3254 sizeof(arena_chunk_map_misc_t)) * (chunk_npages-map_bias));
3255 map_bias = (header_size + PAGE_MASK) >> LG_PAGE;
3256 }
3257 assert(map_bias > 0);
3258
3259 map_misc_offset = offsetof(arena_chunk_t, map_bits) +
3260 sizeof(arena_chunk_map_bits_t) * (chunk_npages-map_bias);
3261
3262 arena_maxrun = chunksize - (map_bias << LG_PAGE);
3263 assert(arena_maxrun > 0);
3264 large_maxclass = index2size(size2index(chunksize)-1);
3265 if (large_maxclass > arena_maxrun) {
3266 /*
3267 * For small chunk sizes it's possible for there to be fewer
3268 * non-header pages available than are necessary to serve the
3269 * size classes just below chunksize.
3270 */
3271 large_maxclass = arena_maxrun;
3272 }
3273 assert(large_maxclass > 0);
3274 nlclasses = size2index(large_maxclass) - size2index(SMALL_MAXCLASS);
3275 nhclasses = NSIZES - nlclasses - NBINS;
3276
3277 bin_info_init();
3278 return (small_run_size_init());
3279}
